# Notes for using design tokens

- Always use `textStyle` for Text components and `size` for Headings.
  - Never use `lineHeight` or `fontSize` directly.
  - Use `color` for text color. Always use semantic colors in theme.ts, do not use hex colors.
    If new colors should be used add it to the theme.ts.

- If you want to use icons,
  1. Use react-icons if possible.
  2. Otherwise, add it under folder `@/components/Icons/svg`.
     > When using, wrap it that icon with chakra `<Icon/>` component to change the size and color of the icon.
     > Search codebase for reference.
     > Do not import multiple times the same svg for different colors. Use the method above.

- For fontWeight, as Design teams request, use only "normal", "semibold" and "bold" for the sake of simplicity.
  Which is equivalent to 400, 600 and 700.

- For page redirection, if not necessary, use only `Link` from chakra.
  - If you need to wrap all the card or box with link, use `LinkBox` and `LinkOverlay` from chakra. Check codebase for reference.
  - Link component has 3 variants, underline, plain and ghost. Choose one according to the design.

- For cards, variant `primary` , `tertiary` is used mostly. If something else needed, add it to the theme.ts.

- Since most of our users come from mobile, we should embrace mobile-first design.
  So always use base style for mobile and use `md` or `lg` property for the style you need to change for larger screens.
  As an example:

  ```tsx
  <Text textStyle={{ base: "sm", md: "lg" }}> Example </Text>
  ```

  - For layout purposes, instead of nesting Stack, VStack, HStack, Flex etc. you can use SimpleGrid or Grid component from chakra.
    Check codebase for reference. This way we can avoid unnecessary nesting and apply mobile-first design easier.
